On certain occasions, the Oskorei may swoop down to grapple with the living, faces adorned in white with black rims.
For two decades, Lords of Chaos has remained the go-to text for how the black metal movement began.
The black metal scene often wins its scores by outdoing itself in terms of outrageousness, blending all things taboo into pure hyperbole.
This is a trend in far-right art that is often termed “metapolitics,” an effort to sneak in fascist ideas in ways that are not strictly political.
The story of black metal has multiple centers, bands repudiating the right, defining themselves on the left, and the families and communities torn apart from white nationalists posing as nihilistic artists.